        "content": "I’m currently unable to complete this process because the SQLite database connection for the tools is down.\n\n- Both `get_db_schema` and a simple `SELECT 1` via `run_sqlite_query` are returning:  \n  `Error no database connection`.\n- Because of this, I cannot:\n  - Create and populate `J09B_temp` from `decision_table`\n  - Add and fill the `ENTSCHEIDUNG` column\n  - Join with `EABLG`, `net_master`, and `sales_master`\n  - Generate the “J09B” CSV\n  - Email the CSV to `meter.readings@evu.com`\n  - Drop the temporary table\n\nI’ve already escalated this as an environment/DB connectivity issue to support by sending an email to `support@company.com` with the error details and the exact tools affected, so the responsible team can restore the database connection.\n\nOnce the database connection is fixed, I will be able to:\n\n1. Create `J09B_temp` from `decision_table` where `TOUR LIKE 'J09B%'`.\n2. Add `ENTSCHEIDUNG` and set it per house (`HAUS`) based on the number of `EQUNR`:\n   - `< 3` equipment numbers → `KSA`\n   - `>= 3` equipment numbers → `EVU`\n3. Enrich the data:\n   - Join with `EABLG` on `INSTALLATION`\n   - Join with `net_master` and `sales_master` on `EQUNR`, preferring sales data when both exist (net used only when sales is absent).\n4. Export the final result to a CSV named `J09B` with the requested columns and send it to `meter.readings@evu.com`.\n5. Drop the `J09B_temp` table.\n\nIf you’d like, I can provide the exact SQL script that will be run for all these steps so you can execute it directly once your DB connection is available.",
